Author: JvdP#8992
Content: So here's a silly question for ya... I figured I'd test the "you own your private keys" mantra of BarterDex and add my privkey to Agama. Worked like a charm (https://www.reddit.com/r/komodoplatform/comments/7tbtt3/using_your_komodo_privatekeys_on_barterdex/). But then I realized, if I claim Komodo rewards now using Agama (native mode), all of my beautiful UTXOs will be gone and I'll have to start over! So... can I _remove_ privkeys from Agama wallet in any way? Or do I just have to start a brand new seed in either BarterDex or Agama and use that from now on?

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: When you say remove private keys from Agama are you referring to exporting your private keys that's always possible

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: @JvdP  You want to delist the private keys from a native wallet so that you don't have that address imported anymore?

Author: Nabob#5004
Content:
in native mode, when you claim rewards, remaining amount move to changed address, utxo's are change which create on address, instead after claim, you can do another self transactionof all your amount to your original address will solve your query

No, you cannot delete your private keys or address  on native mode.

Author: JvdP#8992
Content: @Hermes, yes delist 'em, because the Nabob solution I would have to repeat every time I claimed rewards. But I think it's easier to just make a new BD or Agama seed and work from there ðŸ˜ƒ

Author: JvdP#8992
Content: And anyway, I now know for sure that the privkeys really are mine and can be extracted (as promised of course). It doesn't hurt to be able to verify - learning is part of why I'm in crypto in the first place.
